Speech Emotion Recognition (SER) Bot

[![Streamlit App](https://static.streamlit.io/badges/streamlit_badge_black_white.svg)](https://speech-emotion-ser.streamlit.app)

An interactive deep learning web application that uses a 1D Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) to classify human emotions from audio signals in real-time.

Features
* Live audio recording via your microphone or `.wav`/`.mp3` file upload.
* Feature extraction tracking (40 MFCCs, 12 Chroma, and 128 Mel Spectrogram dimensions).
* Real-time interactive waveform visualization powered by Plotly.
* Complete probability distribution breakdown across 8 core target emotions.

Tech Stack
* Framework: Streamlit
* Deep Learning Engine: TensorFlow / Keras
* Signal Processing: Librosa & Soundfile

How to Run Locally
* If you are on Windows, simply double-click the `run_app.bat` file to automatically set up your virtual environment, install dependencies, and launch the server!
